.TH RDUP-CRYPT 1 "27 Feb 2006" "@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_NAME@ utils"
        
.SH NAME
rdup-crypt \- encrypt files received from \fBrdup -c\fR

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rdup-crypt
.IR KEYFILE
[
.IR OPTION
]

.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBrdup-crypt\fR, by default,  encrypts the data it receives from \fBrdup\fR with the
key contained in \fIKEYFILE\fR. The default algorithm used is blowfish.
.PP
For example
.PP
        rdup -c list ~/Documents | rdup-crypt KEY | rdup-snap -c -b /tmp/storage
.PP
Note the \fI-c\fR option for \fBrdup-snap\fR. Also note that you
cannot change the output FORMAT of \fBrdup-crypt\fR. The FORMAT used is
rdup's default.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
This option is ignored, \fBrdup-crypt\fR always works on the files'
content. This "feature" was added because all rdup-util scripts have
such an option.
.TP
.B \-d
Decrypt the files.
.TP
.B \-h
Show a short help message.
.TP
.B \-V
Show the version.

.SH SEE ALSO
rdup-gzip(1), rdup-snap(1) and mcrypt(1).
